FIELD.name: TYPED_ID
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Raw identifier as typed in the query

FIELD.name: MATCHING_ID
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Raw identifier as found in the database

FIELD.name: Fe_H:log_g
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Decimal logarithm of the surface gravity

FIELD.name: Fe_H:Fe_H
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Metallicity index relative to the Sun, in a log scale

FIELD.name: Fe_H:flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Flag on the [Fe/H] value to express the calculation method (which can be S/M/C/T/D)

FIELD.name: Fe_H:CompStar
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Designates the comparison star from which the [Fe/H] value was obtained

FIELD.name: Fe_H:CatNo
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Star in the Cayrel et al. (1997A&AS..124..299C) compilation

FIELD.name: ROT:upVsini
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Flag for upper value of Vsini ('<')

FIELD.name: V*:Lomax
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Upper limit flag for maximum brightness

FIELD.name: V*:UpPeriod
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Lower limit flag for the period

FIELD.name: V*:epoch
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Epoch of maximum or minimum light, according to: maximum light for pulsating variables (excluding RV Tau stars), α CVn stars, novae minimum light for eclipsing and ellipsoidal variables RV Tau stars

FIELD.name: V*:D_rt
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Duration of eclipse for Algol type stars; Raising time for all other variable types

FIELD.name: velocities:R
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: colon is uncertain question mark is questionable
